50enum class ExprPrecedence : int {
51 /*! \brief Identity(e.g., IntImm, Var) and function call(e.g., floordiv, min) */
52 kIdentity = 0,
53 /*!
54 * \brief Multiplication(*), division(/), and remainder(%)
55 * \note floorDiv, floorMod is marked as kIdentity since they are function calls.
56 */
57 kMultiplicationDivision = 1,
58 /*! \brief Addition(+) and subtraction(-) */
59 kAdditionSubtraction = 2,
60 /*! \brief For relational operators < and <= and > and >= respectively */
61 kRelational = 3,
62 /*! \brief For equality operators = and != respectively */
63 kEquality = 4,
64 /*! \brief And(&&) */
65 kAnd = 5,
66 /*! \brief Or(||) */
67 kOr = 6,
68 /*! \brief Unknown precedence */
69 kUnknown = 7,
70};
71
72/*! \brief Utility used for identifying usage of a buffer_var
73 *
74 * \details Find the Buffer object that corresponds to a variable or
75 * allocation, based on the BufferLoad/BufferStore instances that
76 * occur within the allocation's body.
77 */
78class BufferUsageFinder : public StmtExprVisitor {
79 public:
80 static Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> FindUsage(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage, Stmt body) {
81 BufferUsageFinder visitor(std::move(usage));
82 visitor.VisitStmt(body);
83 return std::move(visitor.usage_);
84 }
85
86 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
87 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
88 if (!usage_.count(var)) {
89 usage_.Set(var, {});
90 }
91 }
92
93 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
94 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
95 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
96 }
97
98 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
99 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
100 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
101 }
102
103 private:
104 explicit BufferUsageFinder(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage) : usage_(usage) {}
105
106 void VisitBuffer(const Buffer& buffer) {
107 if (buffers_visited_.count(buffer.get())) {
108 return;
109 }
110 buffers_visited_.insert(buffer.get());
111
112 Array<Buffer> arr = usage_.Get(buffer->data).value_or({});
113 arr.push_back(buffer);
114 usage_.Set(buffer->data, arr);
115 }
116
117 // The search result.
118 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage_;
119 // The buffers that have been visited so far, to avoid duplicate
120 // entries in the search result.
121 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_visited_;
122};

301 /*! Helper functions for loop printing. */
302 /*!
303 * \brief Print a single for loop
304 * \param loop The for loop to be printed
305 */
306 virtual Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop);
307 /*! \brief Print all simple loops in stack into one line using tir_prefix_.grid(). */
308 Doc PrintLoopStack();
309 /*!
310 * \brief Check whether a loop satisfies:
311 * 1. the loop is serial;
312 * 2. the loop has no annotation;
313 * 3. the loop starts from 0;
314 * 4. there is no optional information.
315 * \param for_op the for node to be checked
316 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop satisfies the above conditions
317 */
318 bool IsSimpleLoop(const ForNode* for_op) {
319 return for_op->kind == ForKind::kSerial && for_op->annotations.empty() &&
320 is_zero(for_op->min) && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(for_op));
321 }
322 /*!
323 * \brief Check whether the `min` or `extent` of a loop depends on previous loops
324 * \param for_op The loop to be checked
325 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop depends on previous loops
326 */
327 bool DependOnPrevLoops(const ForNode* for_op) {
328 auto f_check = [&var_map = this->loop_var_map_](const VarNode* v) { return var_map.count(v); };
329 return UsesVar(for_op->min, f_check) || UsesVar(for_op->extent, f_check);
330 }

334 * \param expr The expression.
335 */

337 Doc doc;
338 // default annotations
339 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
340 std::string annotated_stmt = annotate_(stmt);
341 doc << "# " << annotated_stmt << Doc::NewLine();
342 }
343 return doc;
344 }

346 /*!
347 * \brief special method to render vectors of docs with a separator
348 * \param vec vector of docs
349 * \param sep separator
350 */
351 static Doc PrintSep(const std::vector<Doc>& vec, const Doc& sep) {
352 Doc seq;
353 if (vec.size() != 0) {
354 seq = vec[0];
355 for (size_t i = 1; i < vec.size(); i++) {
356 seq << sep << vec[i];
357 }
358 }
359 return seq;
360 }

375 /*!
376 * \brief special method to print out data type
377 * \param dtype The data type
378 */
379 static Doc PrintDType(DataType dtype) {
380 return Doc::StrLiteral(runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype));
381 }
382
383 /*!
384 * \brief special method to print out const int64_t scalar
385 * \param dtype The data type
386 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
387 */
388 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const int64_t* data) const {
389 Doc doc;
390 std::ostringstream os;
391
392 os << data[0];
393
394 if (dtype == DataType::Int(32)) {
395 doc << Doc::Text(os.str());
396 } else if (dtype == DataType::Bool()) {
397 doc << Doc::Text(data[0] ? "True" : "False");
398 } else {
399 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
400 << ")";
401 }
402 return doc;
403 }
404
405 /*!
406 * \brief special method to print out const double scalar
407 * \param dtype The data type
408 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
409 * \note this overriden function is created as std::isnan of msvc will complain about int64_t
410 */
411 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const double* data) const {
412 Doc doc;
413 std::ostringstream os;
414
415 os.precision(17);
416 if (std::isinf(data[0]) || std::isnan(data[0])) {
417 os << "\"" << data[0] << "\"";
418 } else {
419 os << data[0];
420 }
421
422 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
423 << ")";
424
425 return doc;
426 }
427
428 public:
429 static Doc PrintHeader(const std::string& tir_prefix) {
430 Doc header;
431 if (tir_prefix != "tir") {
432 header << "# from tvm.script import tir as " << tir_prefix << Doc::NewLine();
433 } else {
434 header << "# from tvm.script import tir" << Doc::NewLine();
435 }
436 return header;
437 }

440/*!
441 * \brief special method to print NDArray in TIR
442 * \param arr the NDArray to be printed
443 * \param os the output stream where the NDArray will be printed to
444 */
445template <typename T>
446void NDArrayToTIR(::tvm::runtime::NDArray arr, std::ostream& os) {
447 int ndim = arr->ndim;
448 int tot_dim = 1;
449 for (int i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
450 tot_dim *= arr->shape[i];
451 }
452 T* data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(arr->data);
453 constexpr int NUM_PRINT = 20;
454 os << "[";
455 for (int i = 0; i < tot_dim; i++) {
456 os << (i != 0 ? ", " : "") << data_ptr[i];
457 if (i == NUM_PRINT) {
458 os << "...";
459 break;
460 }
461 }
462 os << "]";
463}

465Doc TVMScriptPrinter::GetUniqueName(std::string prefix) {
466 std::replace(prefix.begin(), prefix.end(), '.', '_');
467 std::string unique_prefix = prefix;
468 auto it = name_alloc_map_.find(prefix);
469 if (it != name_alloc_map_.end() && it->second >= 0) {
470 while (name_alloc_map_.count(unique_prefix = prefix + "_" + std::to_string(++it->second)) > 0) {
471 }
472 }
473 name_alloc_map_[unique_prefix] = 0;
474 return Doc::Text(unique_prefix);
475}

477Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocVar(const Var& var) {
478 const auto& it = memo_var_.find(var);
479 if (it != memo_var_.end()) {
480 return it->second;
481 }
482 std::string name = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
483 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
484 name = "v" + name;
485 }
486 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
487 memo_var_[var] = val;
488 return val;
489}
490
491Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBufferDeclaration(const Buffer& buf) {
492 Doc doc = Print(buf->shape);
493 bool print_factor_explicitly = false;
494 doc << ", dtype=" << PrintDType(buf->dtype);
495 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
496 doc << ", data=" << Print(buf->data);
497 } else {
498 // implicitly define data
499 memo_var_[buf->data] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".data");
500 var_not_in_headers_.insert(buf->data.get());
501 }
502 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
503 doc << ", strides=" << Print(buf->strides);
504 }
505 if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<VarNode>()) {
506 Var elem_offset = Downcast<Var>(buf->elem_offset);
507 if (memo_var_.find(elem_offset) != memo_var_.end()) {
508 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
509 } else {
510 // implicitly define elem_offset
511 memo_var_[elem_offset] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".elem_offset");
512 var_not_in_headers_.insert(elem_offset.get());
513 print_factor_explicitly = true;
514 }
515 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
516 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
517 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
518 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
519 }
520 }
521 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
522 doc << ", scope=" << Doc::StrLiteral(buf.scope());
523 }
524 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
525 doc << ", align=" << buf->data_alignment;
526 }
527 if (buf->offset_factor != 1 || print_factor_explicitly) {
528 doc << ", offset_factor=" << buf->offset_factor;
529 }
530 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
531 doc << ", type=" << Doc::StrLiteral("auto");
532 }
533 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
534 doc << ", axis_separators=" << Print(buf->axis_separators);
535 }
536 return doc;
537}
538
539Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBuf(const Buffer& buffer) {
540 const auto& it = memo_buf_.find(buffer);
541 if (it != memo_buf_.end()) {
542 return it->second;
543 }
544 std::string name = buffer->name;
545 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
546 name = "buf_" + name;
547 }
548 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
549 memo_buf_[buffer] = val;
550 memo_buf_decl_[buffer] = AllocBufferDeclaration(buffer);
551 return val;
552}

554/*!
555 * \brief Check if any optional information exists in annotate_ for
556 * a given Stmt.
557 * \param stmt The statement.
558 */
559bool TVMScriptPrinter::ContainsOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
560 if (annotate_ == nullptr) return false;
561 return !annotate_(stmt).empty();
562}

564/*!
565 * \brief Try to dealloc vars out of space and leave the index to coming vars.
566 * \note It is not a necessary step.
567 */
568void TVMScriptPrinter::TryDeallocVar(const Var& var) {
569 auto it = memo_var_.find(var);
570 ICHECK(it != memo_var_.end());
571 std::string print_name = it->second.str();
572
573 std::string name_hint = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
574 if (name_hint.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name_hint[0])) {
575 name_hint = "v" + name_hint;
576 }
577 std::replace(name_hint.begin(), name_hint.end(), '.', '_');
578
579 auto it2 = name_alloc_map_.find(name_hint);
580 // Skip it if we can not find the name_hint in name_alloc_map_.
581 if (it2 == name_alloc_map_.end()) return;
582 if (it2->second > 0) {
583 name_hint = name_hint + '_' + std::to_string(it2->second);
584 }
585 // Skip it if the name_hint is not equal to how it should be printed.
586 if (name_hint != print_name) return;
587 // Free the conresponding name_alloc_map_ index
588 --it2->second;
589}

591Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegionNode* op) {
592 const Buffer& buf = op->buffer;
593 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
594
595 Doc doc = Print(op->buffer) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(" << Print(op->source)
596 << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[op->buffer] << ")";
597 return doc;
598}
599
600// check if all arguments, except the first two, are specified for T.match_buffer
601// if not, then this match buffer is printed out as T.buffer in prim_func arguments
602// and check whether there are undefined variables in the shape/strides.
603bool TVMScriptPrinter::IsSimpleBuffer(const Buffer& buf) {
604 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
605 return false;
606 }
607 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
608 return false;
609 }
610 for (const PrimExpr& shp_i : buf->shape) {
611 if (!UndefinedVars(shp_i).empty()) {
612 return false;
613 }
614 }
615 for (const PrimExpr& stride_i : buf->strides) {
616 if (!UndefinedVars(stride_i).empty()) {
617 return false;
618 }
619 }
620 if (!UndefinedVars(buf->elem_offset).empty()) {
621 return false;
622 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
623 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
624 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
625 return false;
626 }
627 }
628 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
629 return false;
630 }
631 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
632 return false;
633 }
634 if (buf->offset_factor != 1) {
635 return false;
636 }
637 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
638 return false;
639 }
640 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
641 return false;
642 }
643 return true;
644}
645
646Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintInlineBufferBind(const Buffer& buffer) {
647 Doc doc;
648 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".Buffer[";
649 if (buffer->shape.size() == 1) {
650 doc << Print(buffer->shape[0]);
651 } else {
652 doc << PrintTuple(buffer->shape.as<ArrayNode>());
653 }
654 doc << ", " << PrintDType(buffer->dtype) << "]";
655 return doc;
656}

658// print array out as tuple with parentheses
659Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTuple(const ArrayNode* op) {
660 Doc doc;
661 doc << '(';
662 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
663 if (i != 0) {
664 doc << ", ";
665 }
666 doc << Print(op->at(i));
667 }
668 if (op->size() == 1) doc << ",";
669 doc << ')';
670 return doc;
671}
672
673Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintCommReducer(const CommReducerNode* op) {
674 Doc doc;
675 int n_var = static_cast<int>(op->rhs.size());
676
677 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".comm_reducer(lambda ";
678 for (const Var& v_lhs : op->lhs) {
679 doc << Print(v_lhs) << ", ";
680 }
681 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
682 doc << Print(op->rhs[i]) << (i == n_var - 1 ? ": " : ", ");
683 }
684 if (n_var == 1) {
685 doc << Print(op->result[0]) << ", ";
686 } else {
687 doc << "(";
688 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
689 doc << Print(op->result[i]);
690 if (i != n_var - 1) {
691 doc << ", ";
692 }
693 }
694 doc << "), ";
695 }
696 doc << Print(op->identity_element) << ")";
697
698 // Remove the vars in `lhs` and `rhs`, because they are the parameters of the printed lambda.
699 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
700 memo_var_.erase(op->lhs[i]);
701 memo_var_.erase(op->rhs[i]);
702 }
703 return doc;
704}

706Doc TVMScriptPrinter::Print(const ObjectRef& node) {
707 if (!node.defined()) return Doc::Text("None");
708 if (node->IsInstance<StmtNode>()) {
709 return PrintOptionalInfo(Downcast<Stmt>(node)) << VisitStmt(Downcast<Stmt>(node));
710 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimExprNode>()) {
711 ExprPrecedence t = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown;
712 return VisitExpr(Downcast<PrimExpr>(node), &t);
713 } else if (node->IsInstance<TypeNode>()) {
714 return VisitType(Downcast<Type>(node));
715 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>()) {
716 return PrintPrimFunc(Downcast<PrimFunc>(node));
717 } else if (node->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>()) {
718 return PrintIRModule(Downcast<IRModule>(node));
719 } else if (node->IsInstance<ArrayNode>()) {
720 return PrintArray(node.as<ArrayNode>());
721 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferNode>()) {
722 return PrintBuffer(node.as<BufferNode>());
723 } else if (node->IsInstance<StringObj>()) {
724 return PrintString(node.as<StringObj>());
725 } else if (node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>()) {
726 return PrintIterVar(node.as<IterVarNode>());
727 } else if (node->IsInstance<RangeNode>()) {
728 return PrintRange(node.as<RangeNode>());
729 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferRegionNode>()) {
730 return PrintBufferRegion(node.as<BufferRegionNode>());
731 } else if (node->IsInstance<MatchBufferRegionNode>()) {
732 return PrintMatchBufferRegion(node.as<MatchBufferRegionNode>());
733 } else if (node->IsInstance<CommReducerNode>()) {
734 return PrintCommReducer(node.as<CommReducerNode>());
735 } else if (node->IsInstance<TargetNode>()) {
736 return PrintTarget(node.as<TargetNode>());
737 } else {
738 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not know how to print " << node->GetTypeKey();
739 return Doc();
740 }
741}

781#define TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OpName, OpString, OpPrecedence) \
782 Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const OpName* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) { \
783 Doc doc; \
784 ExprPrecedence lhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
785 ExprPrecedence rhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
786 /* Get children expr out_precedence */ \
787 Doc lhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->a, &lhs_precedence); \
788 Doc rhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->b, &rhs_precedence); \
789 ICHECK(lhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
790 ICHECK(rhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
791 /* Update out_precedence of current node. */ \
792 *out_precedence = OpPrecedence; \
793 if (lhs_precedence > OpPrecedence) { \
794 doc << "(" << lhs_doc << ")"; \
795 } else { \
796 doc << lhs_doc; \
797 } \
798 doc << OpString; \
799 if (rhs_precedence >= OpPrecedence) { \
800 doc << "(" << rhs_doc << ")"; \
801 } else { \
802 doc << rhs_doc; \
803 } \
804 return doc; \
805 }

953Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
954 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->var)) {
955 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
956 }
957 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->var).value_or({});
958
959 Doc doc;
960 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
961 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".let(" << Print(op->var) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
962 doc << Doc::Indent(
963 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
964 } else {
965 if (memo_var_.find(op->var) == memo_var_.end()) var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->var.get());
966 doc << Print(op->var) << ": " << Print(GetType(op->var)) << " = " << Print(op->value)
967 << Doc::NewLine();
968 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
969 }
970 return doc;
971}

973Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
974 Doc doc;
975 if (op->node.defined()) {
976 // merge attr with realize when possible
977 if (op->node->IsInstance<BufferNode>() && op->attr_key == "realize_scope" &&
978 op->body->IsInstance<BufferRealizeNode>()) {
979 const auto* realize = Downcast<BufferRealize>(op->body).get();
980 if (realize->buffer.same_as(op->node)) {
981 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
982 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer)
983 << Print(realize->bounds) << ", " << Print(op->value);
984 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
985 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
986 }
987 doc << "):" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body));
988 } else {
989 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer) << Print(realize->bounds)
990 << ", " << Print(op->value);
991 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
992 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
993 }
994 doc << ")" << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body);
995 }
996 return doc;
997 }
998 }
999 // concise thread env
1000 if (op->node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>() &&
1001 (op->attr_key == "thread_extent" || op->attr_key == "virtual_thread")) {
1002 const auto* iter_var = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node).get();
1003 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1004 var_env_map_[iter_var->var] = iter_var->thread_tag;
1005 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1006 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", "
1007 << Print(op->value) << "):";
1008 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1009 } else {
1010 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", " << Print(op->value)
1011 << ")";
1012 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1013 }
1014 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1015 return doc;
1016 }
1017 }
1018 // default
1019 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1020 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", "
1021 << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
1022 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1023 } else {
1024 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", " << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key)
1025 << ", " << Print(op->value) << ")";
1026 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1027 }
1028 return doc;
1029}

1057namespace {
1058struct AllocUsage {
1059 Buffer alloc_buffer;
1060 Array<Buffer> aliasing_buffers;
1061};
1062
1063template <typename AllocNode>
1064AllocUsage FindAllocateUsage(AllocNode* op, Map<Var, Array<Buffer>>* cache_ptr) {
1065 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>>& cache = *cache_ptr;
1066 if (!cache.count(op->buffer_var)) {
1067 cache = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(cache), op->body);
1068 }
1069 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = cache.Get(op->buffer_var).value_or({});
1070
1071 auto is_exact_match = [](Buffer a, Buffer b) {
1072 if (a->dtype != b->dtype) return false;
1073 if (a->shape.size() != b->shape.size()) return false;
1074
1075 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1076 for (size_t i = 0; i < a->shape.size(); i++) {
1077 if (!analyzer.CanProveEqual(a->shape[i], b->shape[i])) {
1078 return false;
1079 }
1080 }
1081 return true;
1082 };
1083
1084 // If the buffer allocated via T.allocate is an exact match to the
1085 // usage of the buffer later on, then that buffer is the return
1086 // value of T.allocate, and no T.buffer_decl statement is needed.
1087 Buffer alloc_buffer(op->buffer_var, op->dtype, op->extents, {}, 0, op->buffer_var->name_hint, 0,
1088 0, kDefault);
1089 bool found_alloc_buf = false;
1090 Array<Buffer> aliasing_buffers;
1091 for (const auto& buf : buffer_usage) {
1092 if (!found_alloc_buf && is_exact_match(buf, alloc_buffer)) {
1093 alloc_buffer = buf;
1094 found_alloc_buf = true;
1095 } else {
1096 aliasing_buffers.push_back(buf);
1097 }
1098 }
1099
1100 return AllocUsage{alloc_buffer, aliasing_buffers};
1101}
1102} // namespace
1103
1104Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1105 auto usage = FindAllocateUsage(op, &buffer_var_usage_);
1106 Buffer& alloc_buffer = usage.alloc_buffer;
1107 Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers = usage.aliasing_buffers;
1108 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer.get());
1109 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer->data.get());
1110
1111 auto storage_scope = GetPtrStorageScope(op->buffer_var);
1112 Doc func_call;
1113 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate(" << Print(op->extents) << ", " << PrintDType(op->dtype)
1114 << ", " << Print(storage_scope);
1115 if (!is_one(op->condition)) {
1116 func_call << ", " << Print(op->condition);
1117 }
1118 if (!op->annotations.empty()) {
1119 func_call << ", annotations={";
1120 func_call << PrintAnnotations(op->annotations);
1121 func_call << "}";
1122 }
1123 func_call << ")";
1124
1125 Doc doc;
1126 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1127 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc_buffer) << ":";
1128 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers)
1129 << PrintBody(op->body));
1130 } else {
1131 doc << Print(alloc_buffer) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1132 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers) << PrintBody(op->body);
1133 }
1134 TryDeallocVar(op->buffer_var);
1135 return doc;
1136}
1137
1138Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* alloc) {
1139 std::stringstream ss;
1140 ICHECK(alloc->data) << "Should be presented";
1141 const auto& data = alloc->data.value();
1142
1143 if (alloc->dtype.is_int()) {
1144 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1145 NDArrayToTIR<int8_t>(data, ss);
1146 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1147 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1148 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1149 NDArrayToTIR<int32_t>(data, ss);
1150 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1151 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1152 } else {
1153 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1154 }
1155 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_uint()) {
1156 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1157 // NDArrayToTIR<uint8_t>(data, ss);
1158 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1159 NDArrayToTIR<uint16_t>(data, ss);
1160 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1161 NDArrayToTIR<uint32_t>(data, ss);
1162 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1163 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1164 } else {
1165 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1166 }
1167 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_float()) {
1168 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1169 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1170 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1171 NDArrayToTIR<float>(data, ss);
1172 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1173 NDArrayToTIR<double>(data, ss);
1174 } else {
1175 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1176 }
1177 } else {
1178 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1179 }
1180 auto ndarray_str = ss.str();
1181
1182 auto usage = FindAllocateUsage(alloc, &buffer_var_usage_);
1183 Buffer& alloc_buffer = usage.alloc_buffer;
1184 Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers = usage.aliasing_buffers;
1185 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer.get());
1186 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buffer->data.get());
1187
1188 Doc func_call;
1189 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate_const(" << ndarray_str << ", " << PrintDType(alloc->dtype)
1190 << ", " << Print(alloc->extents) << ")";
1191
1192 Doc doc;
1193 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1194 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1195 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc_buffer) << ":";
1196 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers)
1197 << PrintBody(alloc->body));
1198 } else {
1199 doc << Print(alloc_buffer) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1200 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(aliasing_buffers) << PrintBody(alloc->body);
1201 }
1202 return doc;
1203}

1255
1256Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1257 Doc doc;
1258 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->loop_var.get());
1259 loop_var_map_[op->loop_var.get()] = GetRef<For>(op);
1260 const auto* body = op->body.as<ForNode>();
1261 bool simple_loop = IsSimpleLoop(op);
1262 if (simple_loop) simple_loop_stack_.push_back(GetRef<For>(op));
1263 // It is a loop that can be compressed, let the loops below print it out
1264 if (simple_loop && body != nullptr && IsSimpleLoop(body) && !DependOnPrevLoops(body)) {
1265 doc << Print(GetRef<For>(body));
1266 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1267 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1268 return doc;
1269 }
1270 // It is a loop that can not be compressed
1271 bool print_above = !simple_loop_stack_.empty();
1272 // print loops above if needed
1273 if (print_above) {
1274 doc << PrintLoopStack();
1275 simple_loop_stack_.clear();
1276 }
1277 if (!simple_loop) {
1278 // print current loop if needed
1279 Doc current_loop;
1280 current_loop << PrintLoop(GetRef<For>(op));
1281 current_loop << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1282 doc << (print_above ? Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << current_loop) : current_loop);
1283 } else {
1284 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1285 }
1286 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1287 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1288 return doc;
1289}

1294 return doc;

1347
1348/*! Helper functions for block printing. */
1349Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVar(const IterVar& iter_var, const PrimExpr& value) {
1350 Doc doc;
1351 doc << Print(iter_var->var) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.";
1352 switch (iter_var->iter_type) {
1353 case kDataPar:
1354 doc << "spatial";
1355 break;
1356 case kCommReduce:
1357 doc << "reduce";
1358 break;
1359 case kOrdered:
1360 doc << "scan";
1361 break;
1362 case kOpaque:
1363 doc << "opaque";
1364 break;
1365 default:
1366 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown block var iter type: " << iter_var->iter_type;
1367 break;
1368 }
1369 doc << "(";
1370 const Range& dom = iter_var->dom;
1371 if (is_zero(dom->min)) {
1372 doc << Print(dom->extent);
1373 } else {
1374 doc << "(" << Print(dom->min) << ", " << Print(dom->min + dom->extent) << ")";
1375 }
1376 doc << ", " << Print(value) << ")";
1377 return doc;
1378}
1379
1380Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVarRemaps() {
1381 ICHECK(!block_var_remaps_.empty());
1382 if (block_var_remaps_.size() == 1) {
1383 const IterVar& iter_var = block_var_remaps_[0].first;
1384 const PrimExpr& value = block_var_remaps_[0].second;
1385 return PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1386 }
1387 Doc doc;
1388 std::vector<Doc> iter_vars, iter_values;
1389 std::string iter_type;
1390 for (const auto& pair : block_var_remaps_) {
1391 const IterVar& iter_var = pair.first;
1392 const PrimExpr& value = pair.second;
1393 iter_vars.push_back(Print(iter_var->var));
1394 iter_values.push_back(Print(value));
1395 if (iter_var->iter_type == kDataPar) {
1396 iter_type += "S";
1397 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == kCommReduce) {
1398 iter_type += "R";
1399 } else {
1400 ICHECK(false);
1401 }
1402 }
1403 doc << PrintSep(iter_vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.remap("
1404 << Doc::StrLiteral(iter_type) << ", [" << PrintSep(iter_values, Doc::Text(", ")) << "])";
1405 return doc;
1406}
1407
1408Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVars(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1409 Doc doc;
1410 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1411 ICHECK_EQ(block_op->iter_vars.size(), op->iter_values.size());
1412 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1413
1414 auto is_simple_remap = [this, &expr_equal](const IterVar& iter_var,
1415 const PrimExpr& value) -> bool {
1416 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar && iter_var->iter_type != kCommReduce) return false;
1417 if (!value->IsInstance<VarNode>()) return false;
1418 const Var& var = Downcast<Var>(value);
1419 auto it = loop_var_map_.find(var.get());
1420 return it != loop_var_map_.end() && expr_equal(it->second->min, iter_var->dom->min) &&
1421 expr_equal(it->second->extent, iter_var->dom->extent);
1422 };
1423
1424 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_op->iter_vars.size(); ++i) {
1425 const IterVar& iter_var = block_op->iter_vars[i];
1426 const PrimExpr& value = op->iter_values[i];
1427 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1428 if (is_simple_remap(iter_var, value)) {
1429 block_var_remaps_.push_back(std::make_pair(iter_var, value));
1430 } else {
1431 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1432 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1433 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1434 }
1435 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1436 }
1437 }
1438 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1439 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1440 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1441 }
1442 return doc;
1443}
1444
1445Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockAttr(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1446 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1447 Doc block_attr_doc;
1448 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1449 if (!is_one(op->predicate)) {
1450 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".where(" << Print(op->predicate) << ")";
1451 }
1452 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".reads("
1453 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->reads.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1454 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".writes("
1455 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->writes.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1456 if (!block_op->annotations.empty()) {
1457 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".block_attr({";
1458 block_attr_doc << PrintAnnotations(block_op->annotations);
1459 block_attr_doc << "})";
1460 }
1461 return block_attr_doc;
1462}
1463
1464// This function is to make sure arguments of T.reads() and T.writes() is not parsed by printer as a
1465// List. Therefore the brackets are removed before and after printing arguments out
1466Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintExpandedArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1467 Doc doc;
1468 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1469 if (i != 0) {
1470 doc << ", ";
1471 }
1472 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1473 }
1474 return doc;
1475}
1476
1477Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockBody(const BlockNode* op) {
1478 Doc body;
1479 for (const auto& alloc_buf : op->alloc_buffers) {
1480 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buf.get());
1481 body << Print(alloc_buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".alloc_buffer("
1482 << memo_buf_decl_[alloc_buf] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1483 }
1484 for (const auto& match_buf : op->match_buffers) {
1485 body << Print(match_buf) << Doc::NewLine();
1486 }
1487 if (op->init.defined()) {
1488 Doc init_block;
1489 init_block << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".init():";
1490 init_block << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->init.value()));
1491 body << init_block << Doc::NewLine();
1492 }
1493 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1494 return body;
1495}

1498 * \brief Print the name of a block
1499 * \param block_op The block node to be printed
1500 */
1501Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {

1503 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(";
1504 if (!block_op->name_hint.empty()) {
1505 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(block_op->name_hint);
1506 }
1507 doc << "):";
1508 return doc;

1510
1511Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1512 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1513 Doc doc = PrintOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op));
1514 // print block name and block vars
1515 doc << PrintBlockName(block_op);
1516 Doc block_var = PrintBlockVars(op);
1517 // print predicate, binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1518 Doc block_attr_doc = PrintBlockAttr(op);
1519 // print body
1520 Doc body = PrintBlockBody(block_op);
1521 doc << Doc::Indent(4, block_var << block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << body);
1522 for (const auto& iter_var : block_op->iter_vars) {
1523 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1524 }
1525 return doc;
1526}
1527
1528Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBody(const Stmt& body) {
1529 int memo_num_child, memo_current_num;
1530 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1531 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1532
1533 Doc doc;
1534 if (body->IsInstance<SeqStmtNode>()) {
1535 const auto& op = Downcast<SeqStmt>(body);
1536 num_child_ = op->seq.size();
1537 current_num_ = 0;
1538 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1539 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1540 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1541 current_num_++;
1542 }
1543 doc = PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1544 } else {
1545 num_child_ = 1;
1546 current_num_ = 0;
1547 doc = Print(body);
1548 }
1549
1550 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1551 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1552 return doc;
1553}
1554
1555Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIRModule(const IRModule& module) {
1556 auto* op = module.operator->();
1557 Doc doc;
1558 doc << "@tvm.script.ir_module" << Doc::NewLine();
1559 doc << "class Module:";
1560 for (const auto& x : op->functions) {
1561 func2var_[x.second.operator->()] = x.first;
1562 }
1563 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1564 std::vector<Doc> functions;
1565 for (auto it = op->functions.begin(); it != op->functions.end(); ++it) {
1566 if ((*it).second.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
1567 functions.push_back(Print((*it).second));
1568 }
1569 }
1570 body << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintSep(functions, Doc::NewLine() << Doc::NewLine());
1571 body << Doc::NewLine() << DumpMeta();
1572 doc << Doc::Indent(4, body);
1573 return doc;
1574}
1575
1576Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& primFunc) {
1577 auto* op = primFunc.operator->();
1578 // clear renaming map
1579 memo_var_.clear();
1580 memo_buf_.clear();
1581 memo_buf_decl_.clear();
1582 var_not_in_headers_.clear();
1583 buf_not_in_headers_.clear();
1584 // print signature
1585 Doc doc;
1586 doc << "@" << tir_prefix_ << ".prim_func" << Doc::NewLine();
1587 doc << "def " << (func2var_.find(op) == func2var_.end() ? "func" : func2var_[op]->name_hint)
1588 << "(";
1589 std::vector<Doc> params;
1590 std::unordered_set<Buffer, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> simple_buf;
1591 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1592 var_not_in_headers_.insert(param.get());
1593 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1594 // check if this param is a T.handle
1595 if (it != op->buffer_map.end()) {
1596 // check if this match_buffer has only the first two arguments specified
1597 // and whether the match_buffer is a dynamic buffer.
1598 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1599 if (IsSimpleBuffer(buf)) {
1600 simple_buf.insert(buf);
1601 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1602 params.push_back(Print(buf) << ": " << PrintInlineBufferBind(buf));
1603 continue;
1604 }
1605 }
1606 params.push_back(Print(param) << ": " << Print(GetType(param)));
1607 }
1608 doc << PrintSep(params, Doc::Text(", ")) << ") -> " << Print(primFunc->ret_type) << ":";
1609
1610 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1611 // print buffer_bind
1612 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1613 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1614 if (it == op->buffer_map.end()) continue;
1615 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1616 if (simple_buf.count(buf)) continue;
1617 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1618 body << Print(buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(";
1619 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(buf));
1620 body << Print((*it).first) << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[buf];
1621 body << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1622 }
1623 // print preflattened buffer map
1624 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1625 auto pf_buf_it = op->preflattened_buffer_map.find(param);
1626 if (pf_buf_it != op->preflattened_buffer_map.end()) {
1627 const Buffer& preflattened = (*pf_buf_it).second;
1628
1629 auto buf_it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1630 ICHECK(buf_it != op->buffer_map.end()) << "Found pre-flattened buffer " << preflattened->name
1631 << " with no corresponding post-flatten buffer.";
1632 const Buffer& postflattened = (*buf_it).second;
1633
1634 // Call Print() without assigning in order to fill memo_buf_decl_.
1635 Print(preflattened);
1636 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(preflattened.get());
1637 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(preflattened));
1638
1639 body << tir_prefix_ << ".preflattened_buffer(" << Print(postflattened) << ", "
1640 << memo_buf_decl_.at(preflattened) << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1641 }
1642 }
1643 // print body
1644 body << "# body" << Doc::NewLine();
1645 if (op->body->IsInstance<BlockRealizeNode>() &&
1646 op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->iter_values.empty()) {
1647 const BlockNode* block = op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>()->block.get();
1648 if (block->annotations.empty() && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block))) {
1649 // Skip print root block
1650 body << "# with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(\"root\")" << Doc::NewLine();
1651 body << PrintBlockBody(block);
1652 } else {
1653 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1654 }
1655 } else {
1656 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1657 }
1658 // print func attrs
1659 Doc header_attr;
1660 if (primFunc->attrs.defined()) {
1661 header_attr << Doc::NewLine() << "# function attr dict" << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_
1662 << ".func_attr({";
1663 std::vector<Doc> attrs;
1664 for (const auto& it : op->attrs->dict) {
1665 attrs.push_back(Doc::StrLiteral(it.first) << ": " << Print(it.second));
1666 }
1667 header_attr << PrintSep(attrs, Doc::Text(", ")) << "})";
1668 }
1669 // print buffer declarations(buffers not defined by buffer_bind or buffer_allocate)
1670 Doc header_buf;
1671 std::vector<const BufferNode*> bufs;
1672 for (const auto& it : memo_buf_) {
1673 if (buf_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == buf_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1674 bufs.push_back(it.first.get());
1675 }
1676 }
1677 if (!bufs.empty()) {
1678 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << "# buffer definition";
1679 std::sort(bufs.begin(), bufs.end(), [&](const BufferNode* a, const BufferNode* b) {
1680 return memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(a)].str() < memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(b)].str();
1681 });
1682 for (const auto& buf : bufs) {
1683 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Buffer>(buf)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1684 << ".buffer_decl(";
1685 header_buf << memo_buf_decl_[GetRef<Buffer>(buf)] << ")";
1686 }
1687 }
1688 // print var declaration
1689 Doc header_var;
1690 std::vector<const VarNode*> vars;
1691 for (const auto& it : memo_var_) {
1692 if (var_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == var_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1693 vars.push_back(it.first.get());
1694 }
1695 }
1696 if (!var_env_map_.empty()) {
1697 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << "# var definition";
1698 for (const auto& it : var_env_map_) {
1699 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(it.first) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".env_thread("
1700 << Doc::StrLiteral(it.second) << ")";
1701 }
1702 }
1703 if (!vars.empty()) {
1704 std::sort(vars.begin(), vars.end(), [&](const VarNode* a, const VarNode* b) {
1705 return memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(a)].str() < memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(b)].str();
1706 });
1707 for (const auto& var : vars) {
1708 auto type = GetRef<Var>(var)->type_annotation;
1709 if (auto* ptr_type = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
1710 auto* prim_type = ptr_type->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>();
1711 ICHECK(prim_type);
1712 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1713 << ".buffer_var(";
1714 header_var << PrintDType(prim_type->dtype) << ", "
1715 << Doc::StrLiteral(ptr_type->storage_scope) << ")";
1716 } else {
1717 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".var(";
1718 header_var << PrintDType(var->dtype) << ")";
1719 }
1720 }
1721 }
1722 doc << Doc::Indent(4, header_attr << header_var << header_buf << body);
1723 return doc;
1724}

1731 doc << ", ";

1755
1756Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBuffer(const BufferNode* op) {
1757 const Buffer& buffer = GetRef<Buffer>(op);
1758 return meta_.InMeta(buffer) ? meta_.GetMetaNode(buffer) : AllocBuf(buffer);
1759}
1760
1761Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferIndices(const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
1762 Doc doc;
1763 doc << '[';
1764 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size(); ++i) {
1765 if (i != 0) {
1766 doc << ", ";
1767 }
1768 PrimExpr index = indices[i];
1769 if (const RampNode* ramp = index.as<RampNode>()) {
1770 // specify ramp printing as python index slice
1771 if (auto* stride_imm = ramp->stride.as<IntImmNode>()) {
1772 doc << Print(ramp->base) << ":" << Print(ramp->base + ramp->lanes * ramp->stride);
1773 if (stride_imm->value != 1) {
1774 doc << ":" << Print(ramp->stride);
1775 }
1776 continue;
1777 }
1778 }
1779 doc << Print(index);
1780 }
1781 doc << ']';
1782 return doc;
1783}
1784
1785Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(const Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers) {
1786 Doc decls;
1787 for (const auto& buf_usage : aliasing_buffers) {
1788 decls << Print(buf_usage) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".buffer_decl("
1789 << memo_buf_decl_[buf_usage] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1790 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf_usage.get());
1791 }
1792 return decls;
1793}
1794
1795Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferRegion(const BufferRegionNode* op) {
1796 Doc doc;
1797 if (op->region.size() == 0) {
1798 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[()]";
1799 } else {
1800 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[";
1801 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->region.size(); ++i) {
1802 if (i != 0) doc << ", ";
1803 const auto& range = op->region[i];
1804 if (!is_one(range->extent)) {
1805 doc << Print(range->min) << " : " << Print(ana_.Simplify(range->min + range->extent));
1806 } else {
1807 doc << Print(range->min);
1808 }
1809 }
1810 doc << "]";
1811 }
1812 return doc;
1813}
1814
1815Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintAnnotations(const Map<String, ObjectRef>& annotations) {
1816 Doc res;
1817 std::vector<std::pair<String, ObjectRef>> anno_list;
1818 anno_list.reserve(annotations.size());
1819 for (const auto& pair : annotations) {
1820 anno_list.emplace_back(pair);
1821 }
1822 sort(anno_list.begin(), anno_list.end());
1823 for (size_t i = 0; i < anno_list.size(); ++i) {
1824 if (i != 0) {
1825 res << ", ";
1826 }
1827 res << "\"" << anno_list[i].first << "\":" << Print(anno_list[i].second);
1828 }
1829 return res;
1830}
1831
1832Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1833 Doc res;
1834 res << "for " << Print(loop->loop_var) << " in " << tir_prefix_
1835 << "." + std::string(ForKind2String(loop->kind)) + "(";
1836 if (is_zero(loop->min)) {
1837 res << Print(loop->extent);
1838 } else {
1839 res << Print(loop->min) << ", " << Print(ana_.Simplify(loop->min + loop->extent));
1840 }
1841 if (loop->thread_binding.defined()) {
1842 res << ", thread=";
1843 res << Print(loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag);
1844 }
1845 if (!loop->annotations.empty()) {
1846 res << ", annotations={";
1847 res << PrintAnnotations(loop->annotations);
1848 res << "}";
1849 }
1850 res << "):";
1851 return res;
1852}
1853
1854Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoopStack() {
1855 Doc res;
1856 if (simple_loop_stack_.size() == 1) {
1857 res << PrintLoop(simple_loop_stack_[0]);
1858 } else if (simple_loop_stack_.size() > 1) {
1859 std::vector<Doc> vars, extents;
1860 for (const auto& loop : simple_loop_stack_) {
1861 vars.push_back(Print(loop->loop_var));
1862 extents.push_back(Print(loop->extent));
1863 }
1864 res << "for " << PrintSep(vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " in " << tir_prefix_ << ".grid("
1865 << PrintSep(extents, Doc::Text(", ")) << "):";
1866 }
1867 return res;
1868}
1869
1870Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTarget(const TargetNode* target) {
1871 Doc res;
1872 res << tir_prefix_ << ".target({";
1873 Map<String, ObjectRef> config = target->Export();
1874 for (auto it = config.begin(); it != config.end(); ++it) {
1875 if (it != config.begin()) {
1876 res << ", ";
1877 }
1878 res << "\"" << (*it).first << "\":";
1879 if ((*it).first == "host") {
1880 ICHECK(target->host.defined());
1881 res << PrintTarget(target->GetHost().value().get());
1882 } else {
1883 res << Print((*it).second);
1884 }
1885 }
1886 res << "})";
1887 return res;
1888}

1890/*!
1891 * \brief The printer for TVMScript with diagnostic
1892 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
1893 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.
1894 */
1895class TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic : public TVMScriptPrinter {
1896 public:
1897 explicit TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1898 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate)
1899 : TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate) {}
1900
1901 protected:
1902 Doc PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) override;
1903 Doc PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length);
1904 Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop) override;
1905};
1906
1907Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1908 Doc doc = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(block_op);
1909 doc << PrintUnderline(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op), doc.str().size());
1910 return doc;
1911}
1912
1913Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length) {
1914 Doc doc;
1915 // annotation
1916 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
1917 String underline = std::string(length, '^');
1918 doc << Doc::NewLine() << underline;
1919 }
1920 return doc;
1921}
1922
1923Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1924 Doc res = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(loop);
1925 res << PrintUnderline(loop, res.str().size());
1926 return res;
1927}

1929String AsTVMScript(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta) {
1930 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1931 Doc doc;
1932 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1933 << TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta).Print(mod);
1934 return doc.str() + "\n";
1935}

1937TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScript").set_body_typed(AsTVMScript);
1938
1939String AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1940 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate) {
1941 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1942 Doc doc;
1943 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1944 << TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate).Print(mod);
1945 return doc.str() + "\n";
1946}
